cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on natural language processing tasks, specifically sequence labelling tasks, and evaluates the performance of different word embedding methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques and the impact of word representations, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves information retrieval tasks such as named entity recognition, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves neural networks and deep learning, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
